<heading>inspect - Inspect a box in detail.</heading>

<rule/>

<heading level="2">
Usage
</heading>

<pre>
  inspect NAME
</pre>

<heading level="2">
Description
</heading>

<paragraph>
Shows details of a named box at the current world level:
its description, portable items it contains and notes
attached to it.
</paragraph>

<paragraph>
Unlike look, inspect targets a specific box by name
rather than describing the current location.
</paragraph>

<heading level="2">
Examples
</heading>

<pre>
inspect Desk
  Inspect the box called Desk.
</pre>

<paragraph>
Use inspect to examine a box's contents without
navigating into it.
</paragraph>

<heading level="2">
See also
</heading>

<paragraph>
look, go, man, place, take
</paragraph>
